<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-01-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-01-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="84" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-01-25"><hi rend="italic">January 25,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Conger reports that he has forwarded by mail a formal notice given
                            him by the Chinese Government that our treaty of immigration will
                            terminate the 7th of December, as provided for in article 6.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>